  "notes": [
    "Recruiting is uniquely exposed via ATS2 spoke handle; it is both a tab in Talent Overview AND a top-level L2 nav entry (primaryTarget: ['Talent Overview', 'ATS2']).",
    "Talent Overview itself is a container/dashboard that auto-shows when multiple talent apps are installed (see add_talent_overview_to_accessible_apps logic in navigation_bar.py).",
    "Frontend spoke handles differ slightly from backend: RIPPLINGLMS (backend) maps to RIPPLINGLMS key in frontend; PULSE (backend) maps to PULSE key; REVIEW_CYCLES is an internal name in frontend config.",
    "Unpurchased SKUs are cross-sell upsell entries injected by add_unpurchased_skus_if_needed_to_accessible_apps when app is not installed. Currently: ATS2, HEADCOUNT, PULSE, PERFORMANCE_MANAGEMENT (feature-gated).",
    "Talent category's primaryTarget field ['Talent Overview', 'ATS2'] determines which app link is shown as the main category navigation link in sidebar.",
    "No current evidence of 'Compensation' or 'Compensation Management' as a standalone L2 nav entry under Talent; Performance Management is feature-gated and accessible via cross-sell.",
    "All routes use /talent prefix or product-specific prefixes (/ats, /lms, /goals, etc.) as defined in TalentOverview config KEY_TO_URL_MAP.",
    "One-on-Ones is accessible to multiple personas (manager, ee) and shows different content based on role/persona.",
    "The RIPPLINGATS spoke handle (legacy ATS) exists but is superseded by ATS2; ATS2 is the live spoke in navigation."
  ]
